Parameter Selection

Emily Robinson

Exponential with a multiplicative error

Data is simulated heuristically with the following model:

\[y = \alpha e^{(\beta x + \epsilon)} + \theta\] with \(\epsilon \sim N(0,\sigma)\)

where

\[\begin{align*} xRange &= (0, 20)\\ N &= 20 \end{align*}\]
